<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida8c85d0a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s1440"><num value="1440">§ 1440.</num><heading> Annuities not subject to legal process</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except as provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s1437/c/3/B">section 1437(c)(3)(B) of this title</ref>, no annuity payable under this subchapter is assignable or subject to execution, levy, attachment, garnishment, or other legal process.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida8c85d0b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041">Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70A/111">70A Stat. 111</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/92/425/s1/2/A">Pub. L. 92–425, § 1(2)(A)</ref>, <date date="1972-09-21">Sept. 21, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/706">86 Stat. 706</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/98/525/tVI/s642/a/2">Pub. L. 98–525, title VI, § 642(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2546">98 Stat. 2546</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/145/tXIII/s1303/a/10">Pub. L. 99–145, title XIII, § 1303(a)(10)</ref>, <date date="1985-11-08">Nov. 8, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/739">99 Stat. 739</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
